The paper deals with coding theory and information theory, which are typically categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of spatial coupling, which is a technique commonly used in coding theory and error correction, and can be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions compressed sensing, which is a subfield of signal processing and can be categorized under cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing). The paper also discusses the use of Fisher information, which is a concept commonly used in statistical inference and can be categorized under cs.MM (Machine Learning) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
